+{"id":"frankentorch-8kd7","title":"weight_norm_reconstruct severs autograd via tensor_values + non-grad rebuild","description":"weight_norm_reconstruct in ft-nn (line 13718) extracts tensor_values from g and v, computes w = g * v / ||v|| in plain f64, and rebuilds via session.tensor_variable(w_values, v_shape, false). This silently severs autograd: gradients can't flow back to either g (magnitude) or v (direction), breaking training for any model using nn.utils.weight_norm (WaveNet, certain GANs, normalizing-flow variants).

Fix: compose via autograd primitives. Math:
  w[i, ..., dim_idx, ..., j] = g[dim_idx] * v[i, ..., dim_idx, ..., j] / ||v||[dim_idx]
where ||v||[dim_idx] = sqrt(sum over non-dim axes of v^2).

Implementation: permute v so dim is first, reshape to [dim_size, others], compute v*v, sum_dim along axis 1, sqrt, clamp_min(eps); broadcast g and norm to v's permuted shape; divide; multiply; reshape and permute back to v_shape.

Affects: crates/ft-nn/src/lib.rs weight_norm_reconstruct (line 13718)","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"cc_1","created_at":"2026-04-30T23:53:04.695704106Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-30T23:55:25.097942050Z","closed_at":"2026-04-30T23:55:25.095545491Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
